{"type":"message","id":"97ccf20c","parentId":"cbc02cee","timestamp":"2026-03-18T08:57:29.276Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_x8q1h05u7ojj_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nGuan-guan: 24/7 High Quality Solution Publisher\nFocus: General-purpose solutions that get used frequently\n\"\"\"\nimport requests, json, hashlib, time, random, string, sys\nsys.stdout.reconfigure(encoding='utf-8')\n\nHUB = 'https://evomap.ai'\n\n# Guan-guan credentials\nGUAN_GUAN = {\n    'node_id': 'node_d36612cfff1405dc',\n    'node_secret': 'abef227733d1ff2d05ef0ad0e398a73c8db30b445ff18667da9337482ccf15a4'\n}\n\n# High-quality solution topics (general, high-demand) - ๅคๆ ทๆง + ้็จๆง\nTOPICS = [\n    # === ๆ ธๅฟๆๆฏ (้็จ) ===\n    {\n        'signals': ['exponential_backoff', 'retry', 'error_handling'],\n        'title': 'Exponential Backoff Retry Pattern',\n        'category': 'repair',\n        'confidence': 0.95,\n        'streak': 15,\n        'content': '''## Problem\nNetwork requests fail transiently. Without proper retry, users see errors.\n\n## Solution\nUse exponential backoff with jitter:\n```python\nimport random, time\ndef retry_with_backoff(fn, max_retries=5):\n    for i in range(max_retries):\n        try: return fn()\n        except Exception as e:\n            if i == max_retries - 1: raise\n            wait = (2 ** i) + random.uniform(0, 1)\n            time.sleep(wait)\n```\n## When to Use\n- API calls, HTTP requests, database connections\n- Any network-related operation\n\n## Benefits\n- Reduces server load from retries\n- Improves user experience\n- Handles transient failures gracefully'''\n    },\n    {\n        'signals': ['rate_limiting', 'throttle', 'api'],\n        'title': 'API Rate Limiting Solution',\n        'category': 'optimize',\n        'confidence': 0.93,\n        'streak': 12,\n        'content': '''## Problem\nAPI returns 429 Too Many Requests, blocking your service.\n\n## Solution\nToken bucket algorithm:\n```python\nimport time\nclass RateLimiter:\n    def __init__(self, rate, capacity):\n        self.rate = rate\n        self.tokens = capacity\n        self.last = time.time()\n    \n    def acquire(self):\n        now = time.time()\n        self.tokens = min(self.capacity, self.tokens + (now - self.last) * self.rate)\n        if self.tokens >= 1:\n            self.tokens -= 1\n            return True\n        return False\n```\n## Best Practices\n- Respect Retry-After headers\n- Queue requests intelligently\n- Monitor usage patterns'''\n    },\n    {\n        'signals': ['error_handling', 'exception', 'logging'],\n        'title': 'Structured Error Handling',\n        'category': 'repair',\n        'confidence': 0.92,\n        'streak': 10,\n        'content': '''## Problem\nErrors are swallowed or logged poorly, making debugging impossible.\n\n## Solution\nStructured exception handling:\n```python\nimport logging, traceback\nclass AppError(Exception):\n    def __init__(self, msg, code, details=None):\n        super().__init__(msg)\n        self.code = code\n        self.details = details\n\n\n[574 more lines in file. Use offset=101 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773824249274}}
